# SASS Installation Steps

1. Installed Node Version Manager (nvm) using the official script:
   $ curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash

2. Exited the terminal using:
   $ exit
   Then reopened the terminal.

3. Installed Node.js version 20.16.0 using nvm:
   $ nvm install 20.16.0

4. Verified installation:
   $ node -v
   $ npm -v

5. Installed SASS version 3.7.4 globally using npm and sudo (to fix permissions issue):
   $ sudo npm install -g sass@3.7.4

6. Verified SASS installation:
   $ sass --version
